The paper discusses the development of a new open source toolkit for creating and interacting with simulation environments using the Unity platform. The toolkit enables the development of learning environments which are rich in sensory and physical complexity, provide compelling cognitive challenges, and support dynamic multi-agent interaction. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the development of a new toolkit for creating learning environments for intelligent agents, which suggests that it is likely to belong to this sub-category. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the use of Deep Reinforcement Learning in the development of the toolkit, which suggests that it is likely to belong to this sub-category as well. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper discusses the use of the toolkit in the context of Robotics, which suggests that it is likely to belong to this sub-category. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper mentions the use of Unity as a simulation platform, which suggests that it is likely to belong to this sub-category as well. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the development of a new toolkit for creating simulation environments, which suggests that it is likely to belong to this sub-category as well.
